  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"workouts\":[{\"day_of_week\":1,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":10,\"target_duration_minutes\":62,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":372,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":371,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":391,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start at the comfortable end of easy pace. Let the body settle in before finding rhythm.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":52,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":372,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Hold easy aerobic pace throughout. Conversational effort. No surges.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":391,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Wind down gently. This is the transition into recovery, not an extension of the run.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"5 minutes of easy walking or very slow jogging before settling into pace.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"5 minutes of slow jogging followed by light leg swings and calf raises. Given your Achilles history, spend 2 minutes on gentle calf stretching.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Your week of 2026-03-16 came in at 47 km after two weeks above 62 km. This looks like a natural low week, which is appropriate. This plan targets roughly 55 km to maintain your current fitness base without pushing volume up. Monday is a pure aerobic stimulus. Keep the effort conversational. The Daniels-Gilbert zones put your easy range at 5:24 to 6:11 per km. Use the middle of that range today.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":2,\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"title\":\"Lactate Threshold Run\",\"target_distance_km\":11,\"target_duration_minutes\":68,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":372,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":269,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":15,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":372,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Full 15-minute warmup at easy pace. Do not skip this. Threshold work on cold legs invites injury.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":20,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":269,\"intensity\":\"Threshold\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Continuous tempo at threshold pace, 4:29 per km. Comfortably hard. You should be able to speak a short phrase but not hold a conversation.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Recovery\",\"duration_minutes\":3,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":372,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"3-minute easy jog between tempo blocks. Keep moving. Do not stop.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":15,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":269,\"intensity\":\"Threshold\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Second tempo block. Maintain 4:29 per km. If pace slips more than 5 seconds per km, ease off rather than forcing it.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":15,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":372,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Full 15-minute cooldown at easy pace. This is not optional. It helps clear lactate and protects the Achilles tendon.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"15 minutes easy running. Add 4 to 6 light strides of 20 seconds at the end to prime the legs before threshold effort.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"15 minutes easy running followed by calf stretching and ankle mobility work. Prioritize this given your Achilles history.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"This session targets the lactate threshold, which is the primary fitness quality that separates marathon performance from recreational running. Two blocks of threshold work with a short recovery is a classic Daniels-Gilbert approach. Total threshold work is 35 minutes, which is appropriate for your fitness level. Do not chase the fast end of the pace range on tired legs. 4:29 per km is the target. A few seconds slower is fine. A few seconds faster is not helpful.\",\"perceived_effort\":7},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"workout_type\":\"Recovery\",\"title\":\"Recovery Jog\",\"target_distance_km\":8,\"target_duration_minutes\":52,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":391,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":391,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":52,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":391,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Fully aerobic. Stay at the slower end of the easy Daniels-Gilbert zone, 6:11 per km or slower. This is not a training run. It is active recovery.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"No formal warmup needed. Start slow and stay slow.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"5 minutes of walking. Calf stretches and light foam rolling if available.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"The day after threshold work, the priority is blood flow and recovery, not fitness. Running too fast here delays adaptation from Tuesday. If the legs feel heavy or the Achilles feels irritated, this run becomes a rest day without negotiation. The Daniels-Gilbert easy zone tops out at 6:11 per km. Aim for that slower end today.\",\"perceived_effort\":3},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"workout_type\":\"Interval\",\"title\":\"VO2max Intervals\",\"target_distance_km\":13,\"target_duration_minutes\":72,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":372,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":248,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":15,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":372,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"15 minutes easy. Add 4 strides of 20 seconds each at the end to recruit fast-twitch fibers before interval work.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":248,\"intensity\":\"VO2Max\",\"repetitions\":5,\"notes\":\"5 repetitions of 5-minute intervals at interval pace, 4:08 per km. Each interval is hard but controlled. Not a sprint. Recovery between each interval is 3 minutes of easy jogging at 6:11 per km.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Recovery\",\"duration_minutes\":3,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":391,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":4,\"notes\":\"3 minutes easy jog between each work interval. Keep moving. Do not stand still.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":15,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":372,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"15 minutes easy. Do not skip this. Protect the Achilles with slow, deliberate cooldown running.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"15 minutes easy running finishing with 4 strides. Give yourself time. The interval work demands preparation.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"15 minutes easy running. Calf stretches, ankle circles, and light rolling. Check in with the left Achilles specifically.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"VO2max intervals develop the aerobic ceiling. For maintenance, 5 by 5 minutes at 4:08 per km with 3-minute recoveries is a solid, repeatable session that preserves your pace-zone index at 46.7 without overreaching. If the fifth interval feels genuinely controlled, your fitness is holding well. If it falls apart, 4 intervals is a complete session. Quality over quantity applies here more than anywhere else in the week.\",\"perceived_effort\":8},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Aerobic Run with Strides\",\"target_distance_km\":10,\"target_duration_minutes\":62,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":372,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":231,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":391,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start slow. This is the day before the long run. Do not arrive at Sunday tired.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":44,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":372,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Steady easy aerobic running. Stay in the Daniels-Gilbert easy zone, 5:24 to 6:11 per km. Aim for the middle.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":8,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":231,\"intensity\":\"Repetition\",\"repetitions\":6,\"notes\":\"6 strides of 20 seconds at repetition effort, roughly 3:51 per km or slightly faster. Full recovery walk between each. These maintain neuromuscular coordination and running economy without meaningful fatigue.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":391,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy walk or slow jog to close. Achilles check-in before removing shoes.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"5 minutes of easy walking or slow jogging.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"5 minutes easy wind-down. Calf stretches are mandatory given history and the strides just completed.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"This is a prep run for Sunday. It keeps the legs moving without generating fatigue. The 6 strides serve a specific purpose. They maintain the neuromuscular efficiency that supports your marathon pace without adding aerobic load. Think of them as a tune-up, not a workout. The pace is fast but the duration is short. Total stride time is under 2 minutes.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"workout_type\":\"CrossTrain\",\"title\":\"Rest or Cross-Training\",\"target_distance_km\":0,\"target_duration_minutes\":45,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":0,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":0,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Recovery\",\"duration_minutes\":45,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":0,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Complete rest is fine. If you prefer movement, 30 to 45 minutes of low-impact cross-training such as cycling, swimming, or yoga works well. Zero impact on the Achilles is the priority today.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"No formal warmup. Move gently and listen to the body.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Light stretching. Calf and hip flexor focus given the week of running volume.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Saturday is the buffer before the long run. Rest is the default. Cross-training is an option if staying still feels counterproductive. Either choice is correct. The goal is to arrive at Sunday's long run with legs that are ready to run 20 km at a controlled effort. Do not add running here. Your 6-day maximum preference is already met across the week.\",\"perceived_effort\":2},{\"day_of_week\":0,\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"title\":\"Aerobic Long Run\",\"target_distance_km\":20,\"target_duration_minutes\":120,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":372,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":371,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":10,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":391,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"First 10 minutes at the slow end of the Daniels-Gilbert easy zone. Let the body warm before finding long-run rhythm.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":100,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":372,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Sustained aerobic running. Target 5:24 to 6:11 per km. Stay honest with effort. The long run builds mitochondrial density and fat oxidation capacity. It does not need to be fast to work. On a warm day, drift toward 6:11 per km without apology.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":10,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":391,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Final 10 minutes backing off the pace. Arrive home slowly.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"10 minutes easy. Consider starting from a flat surface to let the Achilles warm gradually before any gradient.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"After the run: 5 minutes of walking, then calf stretches, hip flexor stretches, and light quadriceps work. The Achilles benefits from eccentric calf lowering after long efforts if cleared by your physio.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Your long run history is consistent at 18 to 21 km. This 20 km session maintains that base. For a maintenance goal, the long run does not need to grow. What matters is completing it at a genuinely aerobic effort. Your 120-minute maximum is the ceiling. At the target pace this fits comfortably. Your Chicago Marathon result was affected by heat. On a warm training day, slow the pace to match effort, not pace. The Daniels-Gilbert easy zone gives you room to do that legitimately. Fuel every 45 minutes if the run exceeds 75 minutes.\",\"perceived_effort\":6}]}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "modelId": "\"claude-sonnet-4-6\"",
  "finishReason": "stop",
